description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a motivated and dynamic Staff Nurse to join our team whilst covering Maternity leave. We are a 16-20 bedded unit caring for patients with Rehabilitation needs and often frailty. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly Nurse and Therapy led environment which offers you the chance to develop your clinical assessment skills, knowledge around rehabilitation, frailty and complex discharge. You will be confident in your clinical decision making and ideally have skills in IV administration, cannulation, wound management and palliative care. We are a small and friendly team who are keen to support and develop our staff in a positive and forward thinking environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although this is a fixed term post, a substantive post with the trust, at Band 5, will be available on completion of this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 15/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
